\int\frac{dx}{x+\sqrt{1-x^2}}
x = \sin(a),\ dx = \cos (a)\,da
 \int \frac{\cos(a)\,da}{\sin(a)+\cos(a)}
I
 I=\int \frac{\cos x dx}{\cos x+ \sin x}\\ J=\int \frac{\sin x dx}{\cos x+ \sin x} 
 I+J=x+C_1\\ I-J=\int \frac{(\cos x - \sin x )dx}{\cos x+ \sin x}=\int d \log(\cos x + \sin x)\\ =\log(\cos x + \sin x) +C_2 
