\cos a=A(\sin a+\cos a)+B\frac{d(\sin a+\cos a)}{da}
A,B
\cos a=A(\sin a+\cos a)+B(\cos a-\sin a)
\sin a,A-B=0
A=B
\cos a,A+B=1
A=B=\frac 1 2
\int \frac{\cos a da}{\sin a+\cos a}
C
=\frac 1 2\int da+\frac 1 2\int\frac{d(\sin a+\cos a)}{\sin a+\cos a}=\frac a 2+\frac 1 2\log(\sin a+\cos a)+C
